-- St. James's Place assets rise to 44.3 bln stg
-- 
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 02:15AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 23 (Reuters) - British wealth manager St. James's Place PLC <SJP.L> saw its assets boosted by strong sales and recovering financial markets in 2013, rising nearly a third to 44.3 billion pounds.

In an earnings statement for the 12 months to December 31, the company said sales rose 16 percent during the year, spurring 4.3 billion pounds net inflow of new funds.   (London Corporate Finance; +44 207 542 9202)